parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The inability to fill the fuel tank to its full capacity can lead to reduced fuel efficiency, increased fuel costs, and potentially cause the vehicle to run out of fuel while driving, which can increase the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The fuel tank only fills up to 8-10 gallons
the fuel pump shuts off before the tank is full
the fuel gauge shows incorrect readings
the vehicle runs out of fuel while driving.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the fuel pump can cause the vehicle to stall while driving, which can increase the risk of accidents.

the vehicle hesitates to start.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Delays in repairing recalled vehicles can leave owners with unsafe vehicles, which can increase the risk of accidents.
symptoms: Owners are unable to get their vehicles repaired due to lack of parts

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the coolant bypass valve can cause the engine to overheat, leading to potential engine damage, and in some cases, may cause the vehicle to stall or lose power, increasing the risk of accidents.
